1969;;David Copperfield;;British;;Delbert Mann;;Richard Attenborough, Laurence Olivier, Robin Phillips;;drama;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/David_Copperfield_(1969_film);;Charles Dickens' story of a young man's journey to maturity. This version finds David Copperfield (Robin Phillips) as a young man, brooding on a deserted beach. In flashback, David remembers his life in 19th century England, as a young orphan, brought to London and passed around from relatives, to guardians, to boarding school. He relives his struggle to overcome the loss of his idyllic childhood and the torment inflicted by his hated stepfather after his motherâ€™s death. Then virtually abandoned on the streets of Victorian London, David Copperfield is flung into manhood and contends bravely with the perils of big-city corruption and vice; hardships which ultimately fuel his triumph as a talented and successful writer.